Package: leachatetools
Title: Water Quality Analysis Tools for Leachate-Impacted Waters
Version: 0.2.0
Authors@R: person("Robin", "Shannon", email = "rjs@robinshannon.net",
    role = c("aut", "cre"))
Description: Tools for detecting and assessing landfill-leachate impacts on
    freshwater quality, organised around three capabilities. First, end-member
    mixing analysis estimates the leachate-mixing fraction ('LMF') of a sample
    from its major-ion signature, distinguishing leachate influence from
    natural variation. Second, a Bayesian multivariate model imputes
    below-detection and missing analyte concentrations while preserving
    cross-analyte correlation structure. Third, species-sensitivity-
    distribution ('SSD') based potentially-affected-fraction ('PAF') toxicity
    assessment, including a multi-substance PAF ('msPAF' / 'AmsPAF') that
    combines toxicants by concentration and response addition and subtracts
    local background via the Added Risk Approach. Toxicity is derived from the
    ANZECC/ANZG freshwater guideline datasets, with bioavailability and
    physicochemical normalisations (hardness, pH, dissolved organic carbon and
    temperature) applied so that samples are compared on a common
    index-condition basis.
